hopobject.body: Which year are you in? ja pharmacy leicester Despite echoes of bigger-canvas movies in the same vein, like âFearlessâ and âBlue,â the movie gets too claustrophobic, while its noble attempt to take on suffering remains laudable. The goal here is to put us right in the bell jar with Alice, whose visits to two different doctors (Laura Linney and Elliot Gould, in calming cameos) help only a little. Even a twist that seems too pat adds to the sadness. The effort here counts for something, but the emotions may be just too much.
